                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d863">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/7605: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HME1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-16T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 16, 1932—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>118. Your 202, November 3. Have the Governing Boards of the two major parties
                    ratified the three agreements and if so what steps are intended to put them into
                    effect? Please send by airmail text of agreements as signed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
